                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>The Log, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_299">p. 299</ref>,
                    indicates that Admiral <persName corresp="#p_MLL1">Mountbatten</persName> and
                    Madame <persName corresp="#p_CMlS1">Chiang</persName> called separately on the
                    President during the forenoon of November 26. Apparently no memoranda of these
                    conversations were made either by or for the President. <persName
                        corresp="#p_EW1">Elliott Roosevelt</persName>, p. 166, contains a reference
                    to the calls. Presumably the principal subject of both conversations was the
                    attitude of <persName corresp="#p_CMlS1">Chiang</persName> toward the proposed
                    operations in the China–Burma–India theater; see <hi rend="italic">
                        <persName corresp="#p_SJW1">Stilwell</persName>’s Command Problems</hi>, p.
                    65.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
